  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "(*Section E — operatorial factorization of the L=2 SoV basis. Builds a genuine STANDALONE\n  length-1 (single-site) fused transfer-matrix hierarchy t1[λ][a,s] and SoV covector xL1[λ][{s}]\n  (the paper's L=1 construction), then verifies that the s2=0 slice of the L=2 SoV basis factorizes\n  as x2[λ1,λ2][{s1,0}] = c (xL1[λ1][{s1}] ⊗ xSingle[λ2][{0}]) up to a scalar c fixed by the\n  Qθ-vs-Qθ1 normalization mismatch. Sections A–D are read-only.\n  See docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-16-xxx-sov-factorization-functional-overlap-design.md.*)",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*Single-site (L=1) fused transfer matrices — the L=1 analogue of Section A's two-site t2 block,\n  built from the SAME single-site Lax L[λ] (no θ baked in) and shared companion twist G. qdet1 is\n  the single-site quantum determinant: both factors are this site's L evaluated at u-θ1 and u-θ1-h\n  (the internal -h shift), unlike the two-site qdetT where θ is already in T. t1[λ][1,1](u)=tr_a[G\n  L(u-θ1)] matches paper eq. t_{1,1}(u)=tr_a[G L(u-θ)].*)\nClearAll[t1, qdet1];\nt1[λ_][0, s_][u_] := IdentityMatrix[dim[{λ, 0}]];\nt1[λ_][a_, 0][u_] := IdentityMatrix[dim[{λ, 0}]];\nt1[λ_][1, 1][u_] := Sum[L[λ][i, j][u - θ1] G[[j, i]], {i, 2}, {j, 2}];\nqdet1[λ_][u_] := L[λ][1, 1][u - θ1] . L[λ][2, 2][u - θ1 - h] - L[λ][2, 1][u - θ1] . L[λ][1, 2][u - θ1 - h];\nt1[λ_][2, 1][u_] := χ2 qdet1[λ][u];\nt1[λ_][1, s_ /; s > 1][u_] := t1[λ][1, s - 1][u] . t1[λ][1, 1][u + (s - 1) h] - t1[λ][2, 1][u + (s - 1) h] . t1[λ][1, s - 2][u];",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*smoke: shape check for the fused hierarchy*)\n{Dimensions[t1[2][1,1][u]], Dimensions[t1[2][1,2][u]]}",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"352969\" data-output-id=\"174\" data-out-n=\"158\" data-sub-idx=\"1\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"56\" data-sub-start=\"1\" data-sub-end=\"1\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[158]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrns6t2t-9jfh0ts\" data-page-width-em=\"21\" data-latex-b64=\"XGJlZ2lue3BtYXRyaXh9MyAmIDNcXDMgJiAzXGVuZHtwbWF0cml4fQ==\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:2.4em;vertical-align:-0.95em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size3\">(</span></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mtable\"><span class=\"col-align-c\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.45em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.61em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">3</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-2.41em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">3</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.95em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"arraycolsep\" style=\"width:0.5em;\"></span><span class=\"arraycolsep\" style=\"width:0.5em;\"></span><span class=\"col-align-c\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.45em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.61em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">3</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-2.41em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">3</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.95em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size3\">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
      {
       "data": "Out[158]= \\begin{pmatrix}3 & 3\\\\3 & 3\\end{pmatrix}",
       "mime": "text/plain"
      }
     ],
     "id": "9f9d3bd4-1813-4f15-91d6-2d901e3301e2"
    }
   ],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*Genuine length-1 SoV covector (paper normalization, 1-site Qθ1(u)=u-θ1). xSingle[λ][{0}] is the\n  site lowest-weight covector (Section A) — a 1×(λ+1) row. xL1 stays that shape: (1×n).(n×n)=1×n.\n  B1 is the L=1 SoV B-operator. The single-site ν1[λ][u] defined here is the arity-1 companion to\n  Section A's two-site ν1[λ1,λ2][u] (same symbol, different arity — both DownValues coexist; NOT\n  ClearAll'd here so Section A's two-site pattern survives). Qθ1[θ1-λh+(p-1)h] and\n  ν1[λ][θ1+(p-1)h] give IDENTICAL numeric values (Qθ1 is linear, so shifting the argument vs. the\n  function is equivalent) — xL1 is rewritten here purely for notational parity with the Section A\n  x2 fix pattern; xL1 itself never had a bug.*)\nClearAll[B1, xL1];\nB1[λ_][u_] := L[λ][1, 1][u - θ1];\nν1[λ_][u_] := (u - θ1 - h λ);\nxL1[λ_][{0}] := xSingle[λ][{0}];\nxL1[λ_][{s_}] := xL1[λ][{s}] = xSingle[λ][{0}] . t1[λ][1, s][θ1] / Product[ν1[λ][θ1 + (p - 1) h], {p, 1, s}];",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*Internal check (independent of the factorization): xL1[λ][{s}] must be a LEFT eigencovector of\n  B1 with eigenvalue u-θ1-s h — the paper's L=1 SoV property (verified there symbolically for\n  λ=1..5). This validates the whole t1/xL1 construction before it is used downstream. Symbolic in\n  u; residual Chopped at the 10^-20 noise floor.*)\nxL1BCheck = Table[\n   xL1[λ][{s}] . B1[λ][u] - (u - θ1 - s h) xL1[λ][{s}],\n   {λ, 1, 3}, {s, 0, λ}] // ExpandAll // Chop[#, 10^-20] & // Flatten // Union;\nxL1BCheck",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
       "data": "<div class=\"wl-output-block\"><div class=\"wl-output-header\" style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;width:100%;min-height:22px;\" data-session-epoch=\"352969\" data-output-id=\"175\" data-out-n=\"165\" data-sub-idx=\"2\" data-output-format=\"WLLatex\" data-output-is-graphics=\"0\" data-cell-idx=\"58\" data-sub-start=\"7\" data-sub-end=\"7\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;color:#888;margin-right:8px;\">Out[165]=</span></div><div class=\"wl-output-content\"><div class=\"vscode-wolfram-wllatex-prerendered wl-lb-pending\" data-lb-id=\"lb-mrns6tv1-fniretq\" data-page-width-em=\"21\" data-latex-b64=\"XGxlZnRcezBccmlnaHRcfQ==\" style=\"opacity:0.65;transition:opacity 0.35s\"><div class=\"wl-lb-content\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">{</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div></div></div>",
       "mime": "x-application/wolfram-language-html"
      },
      {
       "data": "Out[165]= \\left\\{0\\right\\}",
       "mime": "text/plain"
      }
     ],
     "id": "a6f8ca74-d504-42c3-99de-0b74248d062f"
    }
   ],
   "metadata": {}
